BC (i.e., ultrasound).\n\n#### 4. If you need help recovering or have other special health needs\n- **Services You May Need:**\n  - Home health care\n  - Rehabilitation services\n  - Habilitation services\n  - Skilled nursing care\n  - Durable medical equipment\n  - Hospice services\n- **What You Will Pay:**\n  - Network Provider: 20% coinsurance for all services\n  - Out-of-Network Provider: 40% coinsurance for all services\n- **Limitations, Exceptions, & Other Important Information:**\n  - 60 visits/year for home health care and rehabilitation services\n  - Includes physical therapy, speech therapy, and occupational therapy for rehabilitation services\n  - Excludes vehicle modifications, home modifications, exercise, and bathroom equipment for durable medical equipment\n  - Preauthorization is required for hospice services. If you don't get preauthorization, benefits could be reduced by 50% of the total cost of the service.\n\n#### 5. If your child needs dental or eye care\n- **Services You May Need:**\n  - Children's eye exam\n  - Children's glasses\n  - Children's dental check-up\n- **What You Will Pay:**\n  - Network Provider: $35 copay/visit for children's eye exam, 20% coinsurance for children's glasses, no charge for children's dental check-up\n  - Out-of-Network Provider: Not covered for all services\n- **Limitations, Exceptions, & Other Important Information:**\n  - Coverage limited to one exam/year for children's eye exam\n  - Coverage limited to one pair of glasses/year for children's glasses\n  - None for children's dental check-up\n\n\n[DATA TABLE SUMMARY: **Common Medical Event Summary**\n=====================================\n\n### Common Medical Events and Associated Costs\n\nThe following sections outline common medical events, the services you may need, and the associated costs for both network and out-of-network providers.\n\n#### 1. If you have a hospital stay\n- **Services You May Need:**\n  - Facility fee (e.g., hospital room)\n  - Physician/s